Each of our service is a highly specialized extension. And, we built it using our own framework. Part of this framework is already on open source and is available via Google's SVN server.

\

This is an extra ordinary approach to organize several inter-related websites or sub-domain services using a single controller and centralized database. This reduces the per-site efforts in building and maintaining.

\

There may be a different way to handle the local test servers and real production servers. However, the below links give a way out to browse wherever the script is.

\

Thank you for your interests in our services. You can get much more than your payments, if you work with us and protrude our service for you.

Below information shows the number of files and their overall counter. Now, it is possible to know what files are occupying how much space. This information can be useful in producing a snapshot of a subdomain pack.

This is a rare but useful page. Changing subdomain ID has several resons: You want to extract a database; you want to merge a list of subdomains, and you do not want to lose records from the old system. This list gives you a clue on realtime about what kind of SQL Queries you should run; to change your subdomain ID to a particular ID.

\

Warning:

\

The impact is very big and it is harmful if not done correctly.

\

Hit the query below! Be careful. Do this only when you are creating a new sub-domain from the existing data or migrating into an empty sub-domain.

\

Name Collisions:

\

Few pages like, index, login, logout, ... may collide and cause troubles. This is a runtime (live) system output. It is a 100% trade off; you should:

\
    \
  • either rename one of the the page
    • \
  • or, remove a colliding page and optionally keep or merge the data.
    • \

The text below mentions the public details of a table of your interests. The variables are the control flags that guide the exporter on which fields to export from a table. These settings are later used by the subdomain exporter to extract or isolate a subdomain from the main application development.

\

Once exported and isolated, we cannot guarantee the full support in the exported subdomain. The database might change, and may not reflect on these islated applications. But the other source codes can be used from the SVN server.

This list is a report on our policy to export the system tables. It tries to hide the non-public and commercial applications built on its base, and helps to create a free version of the database.

\

Exporting a subdomain is important when you want to deliver a product to your customer. Or, you just want to clone a portion of your child project (a subdomain service) and discuss with your colleague.

\

Configuring this list will control the exporter on which tables to export and how.
